'''Madras Rajagopala Radhakrishnan Naidu''' (b. 14 April 1907 - 17 September 1979), popularily known by his stagename '''M. R. Radha''' was an [[India]]n film actor and politician. He was given the title of "Nadigavel" for his acting prowess. After a successful career on stage in his early years, he acted in films from the 1930s to the 1970s, and then, giving up films, he went back to his first love

==Career==
Radha came out of his house at very earlier age due to his a fight with his mother as she refused to give him extra piece of fish to eat.Radha was a popular theatre artist who made more than 5000 stage shows. Starting at the age of 10, where he appeared in small roles, grew to a level that stories for dramas were custom made for him.
Radha gained popularity with the success of his stage play ''[[Ratha Kanneer]]''. When he acted in the film version of the play, he quickly gained star status. ''Ratha Kanneer'' gave Radha international recognition and an award. Recently, ''Ratha Kanneer'' has been remade by [[Upendra]] from Karnataka. Ratha Kaneer is his most famous work, and receieved acclaim by veteran actors Dev Anand, Amitabh Bachan and others, saying" that it was one of the most brilliant performances in Indian film history, and that no other actor could ever duplicate that role. 

With his versatile acting, Radha played roles of both villains and comics. After the 1950s, film-makers created roles especially for him, and he often stole the limelight from other actors. He was an active member of the [[Self-respect movement|Dravidian movement]], and was known for his atheistic views. Towards the end of his career, however, he started acting in Hindu devotional movies like ''Velum Mayilum Thunai''. He often used to ridicule atheism in these movies.

==Personal life==
His children are actor M. R. R. Vasu, [[Radha Ravi]], Rashia, Rani and Rathe. By his second wife he has [[Raadhika Sarathkumar]].

==Incidents==
On the 12th of January 1967, M.R.Radha shot  actor [[M.G. Ramachandran]] in his neck. The bullet was permanently lodged in his neck and M.G.R's voice was permanently damaged..

He shot himself on the temple after this incident. M R Radha was admitted in same hospital immediately after MGR was admitted.

He also said ''Naan thaan sutteen. Policeukku statement koduthacchu.''  You could read more abt this incident ibe below link. 
[http://abrahamsukumar.sulekha.com/blog/post/2010/02/an-unexpected-visit-from-mgr.htm THE DAY M.R. RADHA SHOT MGR ]

==Death==
Radha died of [[jaundice]] on 17 September 1979 aged 72 in his residence in Tiruchirappalli.
His funeral procession was one the largest in South India, as nearly 2-3 Hundred thousand mourners paid respect to one the iconic legends of Indian  film, as well as being a key figure in the Dravidian movement and social reform  for all of India. His was survived by his wife the late M R Dhanalakshmi,  two sons and three daughters , M R Vasu, Radha Ravi, both famous actors in Tamil Cinema, his daughters were Rashia, Rani and  Rathe.

